# Thesis Spatial Analysis and Documentation Update Summary

This document summarizes the latest updates implemented in the thesis chapters for the **Geomorphic Spatial Analysis of the Cape Coast Metropolis**. 

---

## 1. Inserted Flood Hazard Zone Distribution Table
The flood risk zone distribution statistics were extracted from the sheets `flood_risk_2000`, `flood_risk_2010`, and `flood_risk_2020` in `LULC DATA.xlsx`. These have been successfully inserted into **Section 4.5.2 (Temporal Evolution of Flood Risk)** as **Table 4.6**. The subsequent tables and references in Chapter 4 have been renumbered sequentially.

### Table 4.6: Multi-Criteria Flood Hazard Zone Distribution (2000-2020)
| Flood Risk Category | 2000 Area (km²) | 2000 Share (%) | 2010 Area (km²) | 2010 Share (%) | 2020 Area (km²) | 2020 Share (%) |
| :--- | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: |
| **Low** | 38.91 | 32.70% | 37.00 | 31.09% | 30.03 | 25.24% |
| **Moderate** | 39.34 | 33.06% | 37.77 | 31.74% | 32.08 | 26.96% |
| **High** | 36.34 | 30.54% | 32.26 | 27.11% | 35.64 | 29.95% |
| **Very High** | 4.40 | 3.70% | 11.97 | 10.06% | 21.24 | 17.85% |
| **Total Land Area** | **119.00** | **100.00%** | **119.00** | **100.00%** | **118.99** | **100.00%** |

