*   **Cobbinah, P. B., & Aboagye, H. N. (2017).** A Ghanaian twist to urban sprawl. *Land Use Policy*, 61, 231-241. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.landusepol.2016.11.020
*   **Crozier, M. J. (2010).** Deciphering the effect of climate change on landslide activity: A review. *Geomorphology*, 124(3-4), 260-267. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.geomorph.2010.04.009
*   **Doan, P. L., & Oduro, C. Y. (2012).** Patterns of population growth in peri-urban Accra, Ghana. *International Journal of Urban and Regional Research*, 36(6), 1306-1325. https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-2427.2011.01075.x
*   **French, P. W. (2001).** *Coastal Defences: Processes, Problems and Playgrounds*. Routledge.
*   **Ghana Meteorological Agency. (2021).** *Climate change and rainfall variability report for the southern coastal zone of Ghana*. GMet: Accra, Ghana.
*   **Maconachie, R., Binns, T., & Tengbe, P. (2012).** Meeting the urban challenge? Urban agriculture and food security in post-conflict Freetown, Sierra Leone. *Applied Geography*, 34, 314-325. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.apgeog.2011.06.016
*   **Owusu-Ansah, J. K., & O'Connor, K. B. (2010).** Housing the urban poor in Ghana's secondary cities: The case of Kumasi and Cape Coast. *Journal of Housing and the Built Environment*, 25(3), 325-342. https://doi.org/10.1007/s10901-010-9189-x
*   **Selby, M. J. (1993).** *Hillslope Materials and Processes* (2nd ed.). Oxford University Press.
*   **Wiafe, G., Boateng, I., & Appeaning Addo, I. (2013).** *Handbook of Coastal Processes and Management in Ghana*. Ministry of Environment, Science, Technology and Innovation, Accra, Ghana.
